<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>Digital Sign Documents</h1>

<p>
    Upload documents, request signatures from multiple parties in a predefined order,
    and record every accepted signature in a simplified blockchain table.
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Users register, wait for administrator approval, and enroll a browser-generated public key using a registration key.</li>
    <li>The private key is saved locally by the browser and is never uploaded to the server.</li>
    <li>Each signer signs the server-provided document hash payload in sequence.</li>
    <li>Rejected documents are suspended until the author cancels or reinitiates the process.</li>
</ul>
